Reasoning: The paper deals with coding and information theory, specifically investigating the maximum coding rate achievable on a two-user broadcast channel with feedback. This falls under the scope of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal Processing). The use of fixed-blocklength codes and variable-length codes suggests a focus on coding theory, which is also covered in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The analysis of bounds and dispersion also involves statistical analysis, which is relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of feedback in the broadcast channel may have applications in multimedia communication, which is covered in cs.MM (Multimedia).
